Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createPinGroup(25.10)                                    createPinGroup(25.10)

Name
       createPinGroup  -  Creates  a pin group for a partition or for the top-
       level

Syntax
        createPinGroup

       [-help]

       [-cell <string>]

       [-excludePin {allLayer | sameLayer | allLayerInGuidedArea}]

       [-keep_out_spacing <integer>]

       [-spacing <integer>]

       [-width <width>]

       [{[-optimizeOrder ]} | -spreadPin | -compact_area ]

       [{<pinGroupName> [-pin {<pinNameList>}]} ]

       Creates a pin group for a partition or for the top-level. Pin groups in
       conjunction with pin guides are used to guide pin  placement  when  the
       assignIoPins  or assignPtnPin command is called. A pin group is a first
       class data object-delete with the  deletePinGroup command.

Parameters
       -cell <string>
              Specifies the name of the module or submodule to which  the  pin
              group  applies.  This parameter is not required if the pin group
              being created is for the top level.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -compact_area
              Specifies that pins in the group are assigned tightly  together.
              By  default,  pins which are part of a group and associated to a
              guide can be spread inside the guide based on the area available
              and alignment to targets. The compact_area  option,  when  used,
              ignores  the alignment and available area and forces the pins to
              the minimum area on guide  honoring  the  minimum  spacing  con-
              straint and overlooking any alignment to targets.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -excludePin {allLayer | sameLayer | allLayerInGuidedArea }
              Specifies  that  pins  in  the group exclude foreign pins on all
              layers, same layer, or on all layers in the guided area.

              * allLayer: Specifies that pins in  the  group  exclude  foreign
                pins between grouped pins on all layers.

              * sameLayer:  Specifies  that  pins in the group exclude foreign
                pins between grouped pins on the same layer.

              * allLayerInGuidedArea: Specifies that pins in the group exclude
                foreign pins in the guide area defined for the group,  on  all
                layers.

               Note:  If  a  guide is not defined for a pin group, -excludePin
              allLayerInGuidedArea option is treated  like  -excludePin  {all-
              Layer}.

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each createPinGroup parameter. For a detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:

               man createPinGroup

       -keep_out_spacing <integer>
              Specifies the minimum spacing between the pins named in the  pin
              group and any other pins, in number of tracks.

              Minimum: 0

              Maximum: 65535

              Data_type: int, optional

       -optimizeOrder
              Specifies that pins in the group are to be reordered to optimize
              wire length during pin placement. Otherwise the pin order is ex-
              actly as specified in the pin group.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -pin {<pinNameList>}
              Specifies the pins to be added to the pin group. Additional pins
              can be added subsequently with the addPinToPinGroupcommand.

              Data_type: string, optional

       <pinGroupName>
              Specifies the name of the pin group.

              Data_type: string, required

       -spacing <integer>
              Specifies the minimum spacing between the pins of the pin group,
              in number of tracks.

              Default: Two tracks.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -spreadPin
              Specifies that pins in the group are distributed evenly.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -width width
              Specifies the pin width, in microns.

              Data_type: float, optional

Example
              * The  following  command  creates a pin group PG_A22 for module
                SH17 and adds the pins pinA22_1 and pinA22_2 to it.

                createPinGroup PG_A22 -cell SH17 -pin {pinA22_1 pinA22_2}

              * The following command creates a pin group PG_A for module SH17
                and adds the pins pinA22_1 and pinA22_2 to it.  No other  pins
                are to be placed between pinA22_1 and pinA22_2 in any layer.

                The pins may be reordered to optimize wire length.

                createPinGroup PG_A22 -cell SH17 -pin {pinA22_1 pinA22_2} -ex-
                cludePin allLayer -optimizeOrder

              * The following command deletes the pin group PinGroup17 of mod-
                ule SH17:

                deletePinGroup -cell SH17 -pinGroup PinGroup17

